Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.61,0:01:24.88,Shiver,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,1000)\blur0.6\pos(30,20)}Just for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.55,0:01:40.46,Shiver,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,1000)\blur0.6\pos(30,20)}Like I used to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.41,0:01:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.73,0:01:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your backs into it, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.67,0:02:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.29,0:02:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that whistling sound I keep hearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.87,0:02:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like birds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.03,0:02:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, a nice breeze is blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.97,0:02:44.89,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an9\bord0\blur0.6\p1\c&H874646&\pos(1282,68)\fscx440\fscy90}m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.97,0:02:44.89,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\an6\fad(2000,0)\blur0.6\pos(1180,110)}The Wind Raiser
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.75,0:02:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a neat trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:02:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to have complete control over the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a stowaway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.73,0:03:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a deal with your captain at the last harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.97,0:03:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I bartered some of this tonic in exchange for passage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.41,0:03:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Traveling by ship is pretty nice, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.51,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see them too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.29,0:03:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're Torikaze, or "Wind Bird" mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.29,0:03:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We mushi-shi sometimes use a stone whistle like this to lure mushi to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone teach you how to whistle like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I get bored, so I just whistle a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.15,0:03:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, these guys responded to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? That's a bit impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.61,0:04:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That one was "Blow stronger."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rest."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.89,0:04:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours sounds a bit off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.54,0:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, they won't obey if it's \Ncompletely against what the flock wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They have their own needs and wants, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.37,0:04:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm in awe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.55,0:04:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But you only whistle during the day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,At night, these guys disappear back to their nests or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. You must never whistle like that at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's likely something bad will happen if you do.{basically mushishi.txt}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A gift for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But it looks really expensive, so I probably can't afford it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'll be able to eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.07,0:05:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ibuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.73,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come over here for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I got kind of worried out there today,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but look at that. We got here long before everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.37,0:05:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really starting to pull your weight around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.55,0:05:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to talk to the owner about \Nbringing you on as a full-time sailor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, our next stop is near your hometown, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.34,0:06:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get there early enough, \Nyou can go home and get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If I tell her I've become a full-fledged sailor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,she'll be proud, won't she{ be}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.53,0:06:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I thought, they're not around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.31,0:06:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damn, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.51,0:06:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nothing's happening, though.{this idiot}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.87,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it down, Ibuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was you earlier too, wasn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.43,0:07:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Cut him some slack today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.89,0:07:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he's just excited to be aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.62,0:07:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.41,0:07:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.49,0:07:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.75,0:07:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The hold is getting flooded!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.61,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did all these holes come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry and plug them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.12,0:07:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Scoop up the water{,} and throw it overboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use! There are too many holes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.07,0:08:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we heard that the ship sank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.42,0:08:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We all managed to make it back on the lifeboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.77,0:08:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will we do now that the ship's sunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you able to get paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.93,0:08:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have this left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.18,0:08:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you waste money \Non something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.37,0:08:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You should take it to the pawnshop \Nand sell it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness, this is trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:09:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to feed the children?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.31,0:09:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What happened to this pot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.59,0:09:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.74,0:09:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was fine just this morning, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.75,0:09:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And just what do you think {\i1}you're{\i0} doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.79,0:10:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't act innocent now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.54,0:10:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.78,0:10:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the stuff you bring is always \Na hodgepodge in terms of quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.55,0:10:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I figured you must have the really rare things tucked away somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Those "really rare things" are the tools of my trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.93,0:10:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I can't sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.53,0:10:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's gotten less trusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:10:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can at least take a look, can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.98,0:11:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a good idea, Adashino!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.22,0:11:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're jumbling up all the contents!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor! Are you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.99,0:11:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.49,0:11:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come take a look at my wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.39,0:11:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She's fallen ill with a strange sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The village doctor can't make heads or tails of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.31,0:11:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A strange sickness, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.18,0:11:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,her skin turned darker yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's getting colder by the hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.55,0:12:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.37,0:12:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, do you know what caused this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.61,0:12:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yobiko, or "Summoned" mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.27,0:12:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yobiko are mushi that bore holes in rocks along the seashore and live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wind blows through these holes, creating whistle-like sounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which cause Yobiko to gather and breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If their numbers grow too large,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.17,0:12:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they can become toxic to those \Nwith a weak constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.85,0:12:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But... why are they here, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.11,0:12:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these holes started showing up everywhere when my son got back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.33,0:12:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your son a sailor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.63,0:12:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The ship he crewed on sank, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.16,0:12:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he brought back some expensive gift, so he's gone to a pawnshop to sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.85,0:13:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ginko,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.21,0:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is there a cure for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.51,0:13:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,First things first. We have to get the mushi away from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.03,0:13:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll use this to lure them outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I leave, plug every hole with soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.21,0:14:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.34,0:14:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This{\i0} is where your home is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.61,0:15:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You're looking better, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.75,0:15:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Doctor, thank you for all your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.94,0:15:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.71,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.85,0:15:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.45,0:15:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it might be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you something bad could happen, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.21,0:15:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just... so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.63,0:15:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.84,0:16:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that stone whistle of yours is—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.28,0:16:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.17,0:16:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The whistle's holes must be made by Yobiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.23,0:16:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And only a few are actually usable as a whistle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why they're so valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.47,0:16:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Find me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.20,0:16:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be wasted on an amateur like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.49,0:16:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yobiko are going back to the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.81,0:16:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.63,0:16:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.59,0:16:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are you going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:17:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.57,0:17:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's unfair?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's always my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.93,0:17:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother's going to die if you don't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.15,0:17:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman... has never been a mother to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.63,0:17:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you recall what I said on the ship \Nabout the stone whistle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.19,0:17:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi-shi usually use these whistles \Nto return mushi to their proper homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, every now and then, \Na mushi-shi uses one for other purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.15,0:17:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who continued to use the whistle for selfish purposes all eventually destroyed themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.43,0:17:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,along with everyone around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.61,0:17:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be no different with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.42,0:18:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you let your mother die like this, you'll end up just like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.91,0:18:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it yourself:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,mushi have their own needs and wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.91,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to bend them to {\i1}your{\i0} needs and wants, \Nthere will be consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.71,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How you use your ability is your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.89,0:18:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you what manner of man you will become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wait for dawn, \Nyou can call the Torikaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.89,0:18:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the Torikaze \Nrespond to the same whistle
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.58,0:18:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they love eating Yobiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.65,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think he'll follow your advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.43,0:19:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.13,0:19:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibuki, why are you whistling at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.67,0:19:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom's very sick, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.11,0:19:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You ungrateful wretch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.67,0:19:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they come!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.76,0:20:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a tornado?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's really done it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.73,0:21:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, the boy was never \Nseen in the village again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.97,0:21:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're waiting for the wind to pick up, aren't you, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.40,0:21:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not come by in the meanwhile?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.96,0:21:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How's {\i1}that{\i0} ship out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.79,0:21:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that one again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.92,0:21:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea how they're managing to sail...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in a dead calm like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.62,0:22:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're using some fancy device or something.
